[2026-03-11T00:27:32Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dpfoc28ynQqDwHgSbSci6o","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Architecture Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and here's a detailed understanding of all the key components you requested:\n\n### 1. **Overall Directory Structure**\n\n```\n/workspace/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cmd/                          # Three binaries\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cloche/                   # CLI client (short-lived)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cloched/                  # Daemon (long-running)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ cloche-agent/             # In-container executor (autonomous)\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ internal/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ domain/                   # Core types (Workflow, Step, Run, Result)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ dsl/                      # Workflow DSL parser & lexer\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ engine/                   # Step graph execution engine\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host/                     # Host workflow executor (orchestration)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ agent/                    # Container workflow runner\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ ports/                    # Port interfaces (adapter contracts)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ adapters/\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ grpc/                 # gRPC server (daemon RPC endpoint)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ sqlite/               # SQLite persistence layer\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ docker/               # Docker container runtime\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ local/                # Local runtime (development)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ agents/               # Agent adapters (prompt, generic)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ web/                  # Web dashboard handler\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config/                   # Configuration loading\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ evolution/                # Self-evolution system\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ logstream/                # Live log streaming\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ protocol/                 # Status message protocol\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ api/proto/                    # gRPC service definitions\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ docs/                         # Design docs and plans\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ examples/                     # Example projects\n```\n\n### 2. **Domain Types (internal/domain/)**\n\n**Key types:**\n- **Workflow**: Name, Location (host/container), Steps map, Wiring array, Collects array, EntryStep, Config\n- **Step**: Name, Type (agent/script/workflow), Results array, Config map\n- **StepExecution**: StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n- **Run**: ID, WorkflowName, State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled), ActiveSteps, StepExecutions, StartedAt, CompletedAt, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage, ContainerID, BaseSHA, ContainerKept, Title, IsHost, ParentRunID\n- **Wire**: From, Result, To, OutputMapping array (enables fanout and output extraction)\n- **Collect**: Mode (all/any), Conditions array, To (join point for parallel branches)\n\n**Validation methods:**\n- `Workflow.Validate()`: Checks entry point exists, all results wired, no orphaned steps, no duplicate output mappings\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()`: Ensures `workflow_name` steps only in host workflows\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()`: Warns on unrecognized config keys\n\n### 3. **Ports/Interfaces (internal/ports/)**\n\n**RunStore interface:**\n- `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, `DeleteRun`\n- `ListRuns`, `ListRunsByProject`, `ListProjects`\n- `ListChildRuns` (for host run hierarchies)\n\n**CaptureStore interface:**\n- `SaveCapture`, `GetCaptures` (step execution snapshots)\n\n**LogStore interface:**\n- `SaveLogFile`, `GetLogFiles`, `GetLogFilesByStep`, `GetLogFileByType`\n\n**ContainerRuntime interface:**\n- `Start`, `Stop`, `AttachOutput`, `Wait`, `CopyFrom`, `Logs`, `Remove`, `Inspect`\n- Optional: `EnsureImage` (rebuilds if Dockerfile changed)\n\n**AgentAdapter interface:**\n- `Execute(ctx, step, workDir) -> (result string, err error)`\n\n**EvolutionStore interface:**\n- `SaveEvolution`, `GetLastEvolution`, `ListRunsSince`\n\n### 4. **Host Workflow Executor (internal/host/)**\n\n**Three key components:**\n\n**Executor** (`executor.go`):\n- Implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflows\n- Handles three step types:\n  - **Script steps**: Run shell commands via `sh -c` on the main git worktree\n  - **Workflow steps**: Dispatch container runs via `RunDispatcher` (daemon's gRPC server) and wait for completion\n  - **Agent steps**: Run CLI agents (e.g., `claude`) on the host using prompt adapter\n- **Output mappings**: Extracts values from step outputs and injects as env vars to downstream steps\n- **Step output files**: Persists to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n- Tracks container runs via polling with 2-second intervals\n\n**Runner** (`runner.go`):\n- Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` and executes the \"main\" workflow\n- Creates host run records (marked `IsHost=true`) in the store\n- Orchestrates via the engine using the Executor\n- Persists host run status to store via `hostStatusHandler`\n- Called by daemon on startup for auto-running active projects\n- Called by orchestration loop to run work\n\n**Loop** (`loop.go`):\n- Manages continuous orchestration with bounded concurrency (`MaxConcurrent`)\n- Keeps up to N host runs active, launching new ones as slots free\n- Staggered launch (`StaggerDelay`) to avoid race conditions on task claiming\n- Back-off polling when no tasks available (30s), fast polling when active (5s)\n- Called via `EnableLoop`/`DisableLoop` gRPC RPCs\n\n### 5. **Daemon (cmd/cloched/main.go)**\n\n**Startup flow:**\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Sweep stale runs (from previous crashes)\n3. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n4. Create SQLite store\n5. Create gRPC server with server-side stores\n6. Set up evolution trigger if enabled\n7. Auto-run active projects (read config, start host runners)\n8. Listen on gRPC socket (default: `/tmp/cloche.sock`)\n9. Optionally start HTTP web dashboard\n\n**Key responsibilities:**\n- Manages container lifecycle (start, track, stop)\n- Persists run state to SQLite\n- Coordinates container workflows via gRPC\n- Manages orchestration loops\n- Triggers evolution on run completion\n\n### 6. **gRPC Server Adapter (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)**\n\n**ClocheServer structure:**\n- Holds references to: RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, ContainerRuntime\n- Tracks active runs: `runIDs map[string]string` (run_id -> container_id)\n- Manages orchestration loops: `loops map[string]*host.Loop` (project_dir -> loop)\n\n**Key methods:**\n\n**RunWorkflow** (RPC entry point):\n- Generates unique run ID (with collision retry, 1-hour reuse window)\n- Persists run record in \"pending\" state\n- **Launches background goroutine** to avoid blocking RPC\n- Returns immediately with run ID\n\n**launchAndTrack** (background goroutine):\n- Ensures Docker image (rebuilds if Dockerfile changed)\n- Captures git HEAD as `BaseSHA` for branch creation\n- Starts container with config (image, workflow name, project dir, network, run ID)\n- Updates run to \"running\" state with container ID\n- Calls `trackRun` for main execution loop\n\n**trackRun** (main execution loop):\n- Attaches to container output (JSON-line status messages)\n- Parses protocol messages: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgLog`, `MsgRunTitle`\n- Updates run state in store as steps progress\n- Publishes log lines to broadcaster (for live streaming)\n- Waits for container exit\n- **Extracts results to git branch** before marking run complete\n- Finalizes run state (succeeded/failed)\n- Fires evolution trigger\n- Container retention policy: failed runs always kept, successful runs kept if `--keep-container`\n\n**ListRuns**: Returns runs from store (last hour by default, or all)\n\n**GetStatus**: Returns run state with step executions and container liveness\n\n**StreamLogs**: Returns log entries (live streaming for active runs, file-based for completed)\n\n**StopRun**: Stops container and marks run cancelled\n\n**EnableLoop**: Creates and starts orchestration loop for a project\n\n**DisableLoop**: Stops orchestration loop for a project\n\n### 7. **Workflow DSL (internal/dsl/)**\n\n**Parser flow** (`parser.go`):\n- Lexer tokenizes input\n- Recursive descent parser builds domain objects\n- Entry point: `workflow \"<name>\" { ... }`\n- Statements inside:\n  - `step <name> { ... }` ÔÇö Define a step\n  - `<step>:<result> -> <target>` ÔÇö Define wiring\n  - `collect all(cond1, cond2, ...) -> target` ÔÇö Define join point\n\n**Step config** (inferred type):\n- Has `prompt` Ôćĺ agent step\n- Has `run` Ôćĺ script step\n- Has `workflow_name` Ôćĺ workflow step (host only)\n- Declared results: `results = [success, fail, retry]`\n- Optional: `max_attempts`, `timeout`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `prompt_step`\n\n**Wire output mappings**:\n- Syntax: `step:result -> target [ ENV = output.field, ENV = output[0].name ]`\n- Evaluates JSON paths; navigates object fields and array indices\n- Injects extracted values as environment variables\n\n**Workflow config**:\n- `container { image = \"...\", network_allow = [...] }`\n- `host { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }`\n\n**Location-based parsing**:\n- `ParseForHost`: Sets `LocationHost` (allows `workflow_name` steps)\n- `ParseForContainer`: Sets `LocationContainer` (forbids `workflow_name` steps)\n\n### 8. **Step Graph Execution Engine (internal/engine/engine.go)**\n\n**Engine.Run(ctx, workflow)**:\n- Validates workflow structure\n- Creates Run record, starts it\n- Initializes collect states\n- Launches entry step in goroutine with timeout\n- **Main event loop**:\n  - Spawns steps in goroutines\n  - Step timeout: from config[\"timeout\"] or default 30 minutes\n  - Waits on results channel\n  - For each completed step:\n    - Records result\n    - Looks up next steps via `workflow.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n    - Handles wiring targets (regular steps, `done`, `abort`)\n    - Checks collect conditions (all/any satisfaction)\n    - Launches target steps\n  - Returns when all steps done and any \"done\" reached\n\n**Fanout support**:\n- Multiple wires from same (step, result) pair Ôćĺ launches all targets\n- Parallel branches supported by collect clauses\n\n### 9. **Container Workflow Execution (internal/agent/runner.go)**\n\n**cloche-agent** (in-container entrypoint):\n- Parses `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n- Creates `stepExecutor` with agent adapters (generic for scripts, prompt for agents)\n- Creates engine and runs workflow\n- Publishes JSON-line status messages to stdout\n- Step output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- Sets `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` from env, removed after read\n\n**Agent adapters**:\n- **Generic** (`agents/generic`): Runs shell commands\n- **Prompt** (`agents/prompt`): Invokes coding agents (Claude Code, etc.)\n  - Reads prompt from step config or `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n  - Outputs to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n### 10. **SQLite Adapter (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)**\n\n**Tables**:\n- `runs`: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id\n- `step_executions`: run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files`: run_id, step_name, file_type (full/script/llm), file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue`: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log`: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n**Key features**:\n- WAL mode for concurrent reads\n- Busy timeout 5 seconds\n- Single connection for serialized writes\n- Idempotent migrations\n\n### 11. **Test Patterns**\n\nFiles demonstrate:\n- Unit tests for DSL parser (lexer_test, parser_test)\n- Domain type tests (workflow_test, run_test)\n- Orchestration logic tests (host/loop_test, engine_test)\n- Mock patterns for store/runtime interfaces\n\n### 12. **Critical Data Flow**\n\n**Container workflow run:**\n1. Client calls `cloche run --workflow develop`\n2. CLI sends `RunWorkflow` RPC with project_dir, workflow_name\n3. Daemon creates run record (pending)\n4. Daemon launches container in background (returns immediately)\n5. Container starts `cloche-agent develop.cloche`\n6. Agent parses workflow, executes step graph\n7. Agent publishes status messages (JSON lines) to stdout\n8. Daemon reads messages, updates run state in store\n9. Daemon extracts results to git branch before marking complete\n10. Client can poll status or stream logs\n\n**Host workflow run:**\n1. Daemon/loop calls `host.Runner.Run(projectDir)`\n2. Runner parses `host.cloche`, creates host run record (IsHost=true)\n3. Engine walks graph, calling host Executor for each step\n4. For script steps: shell command on main worktree, output to file\n5. For workflow steps: Dispatcher.RunWorkflow Ôćĺ step 1 above (nested)\n6. For agent steps: invoke `claude` command on host\n7. Output mappings extract values and inject as env vars\n8. Host run completes when graph terminates\n9. Child runs linked to parent via ParentRunID\n\n**Orchestration loop:**\n1. Loop maintains up to N concurrent host runs\n2. On startup/slot-free: launches host runner\n3. Runner looks for next task (via ready-tasks script returning JSON)\n4. If task found: runs and succeeds Ôćĺ loop tries again immediately\n5. If no task: backs off 30s before retry\n6. Stagger delay (configurable) delays consecutive launches\n\n### 13. **Key Architectural Patterns**\n\n1. **Hexagonal architecture**: Domain (core types) independent of infrastructure (adapters)\n2. **Port interfaces**: ContainerRuntime, RunStore, AgentAdapter, CaptureStore (pluggable implementations)\n3. **Async RPC returns**: `RunWorkflow` returns immediately, background goroutine tracks execution\n4. **Status messages**: JSON-line protocol between agent and daemon (extensible)\n5. **Workflow as code**: DSL separates step definitions from wiring (enables mutations for evolution)\n6. **Output mappings**: Wire-level data extraction (composable, no intermediate variables needed)\n7. **Collect clauses**: Fan-out join points (parallelize, synchronize)\n8. **Git-based results**: Each run outputs to branch `cloche/<run-id>` at `BaseSHA`\n\n---\n\n### **Critical Integration Points for Task Assignment**\n\nIf implementing daemon-managed task assignment with dedup timeout, these are the key touchpoints:\n\n1. **host.Loop** ÔÇö Where tasks are \"claimed\" (ready-tasks script)\n2. **host.Executor** ÔÇö Where output mappings inject task ID\n3. **host.Runner** ÔÇö Where host run state is persisted\n4. **RunStore** ÔÇö Where dedup timeout state would be tracked\n5. **gRPC server** ÔÇö Where task lifecycle events could be published\n6. **Protocol messages** ÔÇö Where task status could be streamed\n\n**All file paths are absolute paths starting from `/workspace/`.**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a883f3608fbd6f31a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77431\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 123904</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f8bcbbf-b8aa-4f20-9779-dee3a5fa668b","uuid":"d74c2cae-d4bf-46f3-a8da-749c794c2430","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the Cloche project structure very thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall directory structure (cmd/, internal/, etc.)\n2. The host workflow executor (internal/host/) - how it works, what it does\n3. The daemon (cmd/cloched/, and any internal packages it uses) - how it manages runs\n4. The domain types (internal/domain/) - especially Workflow, Step, Run, Result\n5. The ports/interfaces (internal/ports/) - especially RunStore, AgentAdapter, any task-related interfaces\n6. The adapters (internal/adapters/) - especially how container workflows are dispatched\n7. Any existing task-related functionality (list-tasks, task assignment, etc.)\n8. The workflow DSL - how workflows are defined and parsed\n9. Any existing test patterns\n\nBe very thorough - read key files in full. I need to understand the architecture deeply to implement daemon-managed task assignment with dedup timeout.","agentId":"a883f3608fbd6f31a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Architecture Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and here's a detailed understanding of all the key components you requested:\n\n### 1. **Overall Directory Structure**\n\n```\n/workspace/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cmd/                          # Three binaries\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cloche/                   # CLI client (short-lived)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ cloched/                  # Daemon (long-running)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ cloche-agent/             # In-container executor (autonomous)\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ internal/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ domain/                   # Core types (Workflow, Step, Run, Result)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ dsl/                      # Workflow DSL parser & lexer\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ engine/                   # Step graph execution engine\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host/                     # Host workflow executor (orchestration)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ agent/                    # Container workflow runner\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ ports/                    # Port interfaces (adapter contracts)\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ adapters/\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ grpc/                 # gRPC server (daemon RPC endpoint)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ sqlite/               # SQLite persistence layer\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ docker/               # Docker container runtime\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ local/                # Local runtime (development)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ agents/               # Agent adapters (prompt, generic)\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ web/                  # Web dashboard handler\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config/                   # Configuration loading\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ evolution/                # Self-evolution system\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ logstream/                # Live log streaming\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ protocol/                 # Status message protocol\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ api/proto/                    # gRPC service definitions\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ docs/                         # Design docs and plans\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ examples/                     # Example projects\n```\n\n### 2. **Domain Types (internal/domain/)**\n\n**Key types:**\n- **Workflow**: Name, Location (host/container), Steps map, Wiring array, Collects array, EntryStep, Config\n- **Step**: Name, Type (agent/script/workflow), Results array, Config map\n- **StepExecution**: StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n- **Run**: ID, WorkflowName, State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled), ActiveSteps, StepExecutions, StartedAt, CompletedAt, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage, ContainerID, BaseSHA, ContainerKept, Title, IsHost, ParentRunID\n- **Wire**: From, Result, To, OutputMapping array (enables fanout and output extraction)\n- **Collect**: Mode (all/any), Conditions array, To (join point for parallel branches)\n\n**Validation methods:**\n- `Workflow.Validate()`: Checks entry point exists, all results wired, no orphaned steps, no duplicate output mappings\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()`: Ensures `workflow_name` steps only in host workflows\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()`: Warns on unrecognized config keys\n\n### 3. **Ports/Interfaces (internal/ports/)**\n\n**RunStore interface:**\n- `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, `DeleteRun`\n- `ListRuns`, `ListRunsByProject`, `ListProjects`\n- `ListChildRuns` (for host run hierarchies)\n\n**CaptureStore interface:**\n- `SaveCapture`, `GetCaptures` (step execution snapshots)\n\n**LogStore interface:**\n- `SaveLogFile`, `GetLogFiles`, `GetLogFilesByStep`, `GetLogFileByType`\n\n**ContainerRuntime interface:**\n- `Start`, `Stop`, `AttachOutput`, `Wait`, `CopyFrom`, `Logs`, `Remove`, `Inspect`\n- Optional: `EnsureImage` (rebuilds if Dockerfile changed)\n\n**AgentAdapter interface:**\n- `Execute(ctx, step, workDir) -> (result string, err error)`\n\n**EvolutionStore interface:**\n- `SaveEvolution`, `GetLastEvolution`, `ListRunsSince`\n\n### 4. **Host Workflow Executor (internal/host/)**\n\n**Three key components:**\n\n**Executor** (`executor.go`):\n- Implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflows\n- Handles three step types:\n  - **Script steps**: Run shell commands via `sh -c` on the main git worktree\n  - **Workflow steps**: Dispatch container runs via `RunDispatcher` (daemon's gRPC server) and wait for completion\n  - **Agent steps**: Run CLI agents (e.g., `claude`) on the host using prompt adapter\n- **Output mappings**: Extracts values from step outputs and injects as env vars to downstream steps\n- **Step output files**: Persists to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n- Tracks container runs via polling with 2-second intervals\n\n**Runner** (`runner.go`):\n- Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` and executes the \"main\" workflow\n- Creates host run records (marked `IsHost=true`) in the store\n- Orchestrates via the engine using the Executor\n- Persists host run status to store via `hostStatusHandler`\n- Called by daemon on startup for auto-running active projects\n- Called by orchestration loop to run work\n\n**Loop** (`loop.go`):\n- Manages continuous orchestration with bounded concurrency (`MaxConcurrent`)\n- Keeps up to N host runs active, launching new ones as slots free\n- Staggered launch (`StaggerDelay`) to avoid race conditions on task claiming\n- Back-off polling when no tasks available (30s), fast polling when active (5s)\n- Called via `EnableLoop`/`DisableLoop` gRPC RPCs\n\n### 5. **Daemon (cmd/cloched/main.go)**\n\n**Startup flow:**\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Sweep stale runs (from previous crashes)\n3. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n4. Create SQLite store\n5. Create gRPC server with server-side stores\n6. Set up evolution trigger if enabled\n7. Auto-run active projects (read config, start host runners)\n8. Listen on gRPC socket (default: `/tmp/cloche.sock`)\n9. Optionally start HTTP web dashboard\n\n**Key responsibilities:**\n- Manages container lifecycle (start, track, stop)\n- Persists run state to SQLite\n- Coordinates container workflows via gRPC\n- Manages orchestration loops\n- Triggers evolution on run completion\n\n### 6. **gRPC Server Adapter (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)**\n\n**ClocheServer structure:**\n- Holds references to: RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, ContainerRuntime\n- Tracks active runs: `runIDs map[string]string` (run_id -> container_id)\n- Manages orchestration loops: `loops map[string]*host.Loop` (project_dir -> loop)\n\n**Key methods:**\n\n**RunWorkflow** (RPC entry point):\n- Generates unique run ID (with collision retry, 1-hour reuse window)\n- Persists run record in \"pending\" state\n- **Launches background goroutine** to avoid blocking RPC\n- Returns immediately with run ID\n\n**launchAndTrack** (background goroutine):\n- Ensures Docker image (rebuilds if Dockerfile changed)\n- Captures git HEAD as `BaseSHA` for branch creation\n- Starts container with config (image, workflow name, project dir, network, run ID)\n- Updates run to \"running\" state with container ID\n- Calls `trackRun` for main execution loop\n\n**trackRun** (main execution loop):\n- Attaches to container output (JSON-line status messages)\n- Parses protocol messages: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgLog`, `MsgRunTitle`\n- Updates run state in store as steps progress\n- Publishes log lines to broadcaster (for live streaming)\n- Waits for container exit\n- **Extracts results to git branch** before marking run complete\n- Finalizes run state (succeeded/failed)\n- Fires evolution trigger\n- Container retention policy: failed runs always kept, successful runs kept if `--keep-container`\n\n**ListRuns**: Returns runs from store (last hour by default, or all)\n\n**GetStatus**: Returns run state with step executions and container liveness\n\n**StreamLogs**: Returns log entries (live streaming for active runs, file-based for completed)\n\n**StopRun**: Stops container and marks run cancelled\n\n**EnableLoop**: Creates and starts orchestration loop for a project\n\n**DisableLoop**: Stops orchestration loop for a project\n\n### 7. **Workflow DSL (internal/dsl/)**\n\n**Parser flow** (`parser.go`):\n- Lexer tokenizes input\n- Recursive descent parser builds domain objects\n- Entry point: `workflow \"<name>\" { ... }`\n- Statements inside:\n  - `step <name> { ... }` ÔÇö Define a step\n  - `<step>:<result> -> <target>` ÔÇö Define wiring\n  - `collect all(cond1, cond2, ...) -> target` ÔÇö Define join point\n\n**Step config** (inferred type):\n- Has `prompt` Ôćĺ agent step\n- Has `run` Ôćĺ script step\n- Has `workflow_name` Ôćĺ workflow step (host only)\n- Declared results: `results = [success, fail, retry]`\n- Optional: `max_attempts`, `timeout`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `prompt_step`\n\n**Wire output mappings**:\n- Syntax: `step:result -> target [ ENV = output.field, ENV = output[0].name ]`\n- Evaluates JSON paths; navigates object fields and array indices\n- Injects extracted values as environment variables\n\n**Workflow config**:\n- `container { image = \"...\", network_allow = [...] }`\n- `host { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }`\n\n**Location-based parsing**:\n- `ParseForHost`: Sets `LocationHost` (allows `workflow_name` steps)\n- `ParseForContainer`: Sets `LocationContainer` (forbids `workflow_name` steps)\n\n### 8. **Step Graph Execution Engine (internal/engine/engine.go)**\n\n**Engine.Run(ctx, workflow)**:\n- Validates workflow structure\n- Creates Run record, starts it\n- Initializes collect states\n- Launches entry step in goroutine with timeout\n- **Main event loop**:\n  - Spawns steps in goroutines\n  - Step timeout: from config[\"timeout\"] or default 30 minutes\n  - Waits on results channel\n  - For each completed step:\n    - Records result\n    - Looks up next steps via `workflow.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n    - Handles wiring targets (regular steps, `done`, `abort`)\n    - Checks collect conditions (all/any satisfaction)\n    - Launches target steps\n  - Returns when all steps done and any \"done\" reached\n\n**Fanout support**:\n- Multiple wires from same (step, result) pair Ôćĺ launches all targets\n- Parallel branches supported by collect clauses\n\n### 9. **Container Workflow Execution (internal/agent/runner.go)**\n\n**cloche-agent** (in-container entrypoint):\n- Parses `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n- Creates `stepExecutor` with agent adapters (generic for scripts, prompt for agents)\n- Creates engine and runs workflow\n- Publishes JSON-line status messages to stdout\n- Step output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- Sets `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` from env, removed after read\n\n**Agent adapters**:\n- **Generic** (`agents/generic`): Runs shell commands\n- **Prompt** (`agents/prompt`): Invokes coding agents (Claude Code, etc.)\n  - Reads prompt from step config or `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n  - Outputs to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n### 10. **SQLite Adapter (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)**\n\n**Tables**:\n- `runs`: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id\n- `step_executions`: run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files`: run_id, step_name, file_type (full/script/llm), file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue`: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log`: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n**Key features**:\n- WAL mode for concurrent reads\n- Busy timeout 5 seconds\n- Single connection for serialized writes\n- Idempotent migrations\n\n### 11. **Test Patterns**\n\nFiles demonstrate:\n- Unit tests for DSL parser (lexer_test, parser_test)\n- Domain type tests (workflow_test, run_test)\n- Orchestration logic tests (host/loop_test, engine_test)\n- Mock patterns for store/runtime interfaces\n\n### 12. **Critical Data Flow**\n\n**Container workflow run:**\n1. Client calls `cloche run --workflow develop`\n2. CLI sends `RunWorkflow` RPC with project_dir, workflow_name\n3. Daemon creates run record (pending)\n4. Daemon launches container in background (returns immediately)\n5. Container starts `cloche-agent develop.cloche`\n6. Agent parses workflow, executes step graph\n7. Agent publishes status messages (JSON lines) to stdout\n8. Daemon reads messages, updates run state in store\n9. Daemon extracts results to git branch before marking complete\n10. Client can poll status or stream logs\n\n**Host workflow run:**\n1. Daemon/loop calls `host.Runner.Run(projectDir)`\n2. Runner parses `host.cloche`, creates host run record (IsHost=true)\n3. Engine walks graph, calling host Executor for each step\n4. For script steps: shell command on main worktree, output to file\n5. For workflow steps: Dispatcher.RunWorkflow Ôćĺ step 1 above (nested)\n6. For agent steps: invoke `claude` command on host\n7. Output mappings extract values and inject as env vars\n8. Host run completes when graph terminates\n9. Child runs linked to parent via ParentRunID\n\n**Orchestration loop:**\n1. Loop maintains up to N concurrent host runs\n2. On startup/slot-free: launches host runner\n3. Runner looks for next task (via ready-tasks script returning JSON)\n4. If task found: runs and succeeds Ôćĺ loop tries again immediately\n5. If no task: backs off 30s before retry\n6. Stagger delay (configurable) delays consecutive launches\n\n### 13. **Key Architectural Patterns**\n\n1. **Hexagonal architecture**: Domain (core types) independent of infrastructure (adapters)\n2. **Port interfaces**: ContainerRuntime, RunStore, AgentAdapter, CaptureStore (pluggable implementations)\n3. **Async RPC returns**: `RunWorkflow` returns immediately, background goroutine tracks execution\n4. **Status messages**: JSON-line protocol between agent and daemon (extensible)\n5. **Workflow as code**: DSL separates step definitions from wiring (enables mutations for evolution)\n6. **Output mappings**: Wire-level data extraction (composable, no intermediate variables needed)\n7. **Collect clauses**: Fan-out join points (parallelize, synchronize)\n8. **Git-based results**: Each run outputs to branch `cloche/<run-id>` at `BaseSHA`\n\n---\n\n### **Critical Integration Points for Task Assignment**\n\nIf implementing daemon-managed task assignment with dedup timeout, these are the key touchpoints:\n\n1. **host.Loop** ÔÇö Where tasks are \"claimed\" (ready-tasks script)\n2. **host.Executor** ÔÇö Where output mappings inject task ID\n3. **host.Runner** ÔÇö Where host run state is persisted\n4. **RunStore** ÔÇö Where dedup timeout state would be tracked\n5. **gRPC server** ÔÇö Where task lifecycle events could be published\n6. **Protocol messages** ÔÇö Where task status could be streamed\n\n**All file paths are absolute paths starting from `/workspace/`.**"}],"totalDurationMs":123904,"totalTokens":77431,"totalToolUseCount":44,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2640,"cache_read_input_tokens":70784,"output_tokens":4007,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2640},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
