[2026-03-11T00:27:32Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AEgMTcQZ46iWtWxpX4mVMc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺpackage main\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺimport (\n     4Ôćĺ\t\"fmt\"\n     5Ôćĺ\t\"os\"\n     6Ôćĺ\t\"path/filepath\"\n     7Ôćĺ\t\"strings\"\n     8Ôćĺ)\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺvar workflowTemplate = `workflow \"%s\" {\n    11Ôćĺ  step implement {\n    12Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    13Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    14Ôćĺ  }\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ  step test {\n    17Ôćĺ    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    18Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    19Ôćĺ  }\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21Ôćĺ  step fix {\n    22Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    23Ôćĺ    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    24Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n    25Ôćĺ  }\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ  step update-docs {\n    28Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/update-docs.md\")\n    29Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    30Ôćĺ  }\n    31Ôćĺ\n    32Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n    33Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n    34Ôćĺ  test:success -> update-docs\n    35Ôćĺ  test:fail -> fix\n    36Ôćĺ  fix:success -> test\n    37Ôćĺ  fix:fail -> abort\n    38Ôćĺ  fix:give-up -> abort\n    39Ôćĺ  update-docs:success -> done\n    40Ôćĺ  update-docs:fail -> done\n    41Ôćĺ}\n    42Ôćĺ`\n    43Ôćĺ\n    44Ôćĺvar dockerfileTemplate = `FROM %s\n    45ÔćĺUSER root\n    46Ôćĺ\n    47Ôćĺ# Add your project's dependencies here.\n    48Ôćĺ# Example:\n    49Ôćĺ#   RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    50Ôćĺ#   RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    51Ôćĺ\n    52ÔćĺUSER agent\n    53Ôćĺ`\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺvar implementPrompt = `Implement the following change in this project.\n    56Ôćĺ\n    57Ôćĺ## User Request\n    58Ôćĺ(Contents of .cloche/prompt.txt will be injected here by the adapter)\n    59Ôćĺ\n    60Ôćĺ## Guidelines\n    61Ôćĺ- Follow existing project conventions if files already exist\n    62Ôćĺ- Write tests for new functionality\n    63Ôćĺ- Run tests locally before declaring success\n    64Ôćĺ`\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺvar fixPrompt = `Fix the code based on the validation failures below.\n    67ÔćĺOnly modify files that need fixing. Do not rewrite the entire project.\n    68Ôćĺ\n    69Ôćĺ## Validation Output\n    70Ôćĺ(Contents of .cloche/output/*.log will be injected here by the adapter)\n    71Ôćĺ`\n    72Ôćĺ\n    73Ôćĺvar defaultConfigTOML = `# Cloche project configuration\n    74Ôćĺ# Set active = true so cloched auto-runs the main workflow on startup.\n    75Ôćĺactive = false\n    76Ôćĺ\n    77Ôćĺ[evolution]\n    78Ôćĺenabled            = true\n    79Ôćĺdebounce_seconds   = 30\n    80Ôćĺmin_confidence     = \"medium\"\n    81Ôćĺmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n    82Ôćĺ`\n    83Ôćĺ\n    84Ôćĺvar updateDocsPrompt = `Review the CLI source code and update usage documentation to reflect any changes.\n    85Ôćĺ\n    86Ôćĺ## What to check\n    87Ôćĺ1. Read cmd/cloche/main.go and cmd/cloche/init.go to understand the current CLI surface\n    88Ôćĺ2. Compare against docs/USAGE.md\n    89Ôćĺ\n    90Ôćĺ## Sections to keep in sync\n    91Ôćĺ- CLI Reference: subcommands, flags, usage examples\n    92Ôćĺ- Setting Up a New Project: scaffolding steps, workflow template\n    93Ôćĺ- Daemon Configuration: environment variables\n    94Ôćĺ- Build Commands: Makefile targets\n    95Ôćĺ\n    96Ôćĺ## Rules\n    97Ôćĺ- Only modify docs/USAGE.md (and docs/workflows.md if workflow DSL syntax changed)\n    98Ôćĺ- Only make changes when there are actual discrepancies ÔÇö do not rewrite for style\n    99Ôćĺ- If everything is already accurate, make no changes and report success\n   100Ôćĺ`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PBzqGrRSxSxC8pWZNjvguQ","session_id":"2f8bcbbf-b8aa-4f20-9779-dee3a5fa668b","uuid":"8555bb53-7f8a-4929-9893-4fbb2cdd625b"}
