[2026-03-11T00:27:32Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HQmEytPMcTYiWeUYSrhwrc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0151XVf5gKitzUzkZ6wLGxbE","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md","offset":100,"limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1339,"cache_read_input_tokens":62875,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1339,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PBzqGrRSxSxC8pWZNjvguQ","session_id":"2f8bcbbf-b8aa-4f20-9779-dee3a5fa668b","uuid":"79713714-b630-4313-92ad-970c1a620a49"}
[2026-03-11T00:27:32Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0151XVf5gKitzUzkZ6wLGxbE","type":"tool_result","content":"   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ## Wire Output Mappings\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103ÔćĺWires can include output mappings that extract values from a step's output and inject\n   104Ôćĺthem as environment variables into the target step:\n   105Ôćĺ\n   106Ôćĺ```\n   107Ôćĺstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   108Ôćĺ```\n   109Ôćĺ\n   110ÔćĺThe general form:\n   111Ôćĺ\n   112Ôćĺ```\n   113ÔćĺFROM:RESULT -> TO [ KEY = EXPR, KEY = EXPR, ... ]\n   114Ôćĺ```\n   115Ôćĺ\n   116ÔćĺWhere `KEY` is the environment variable name and `EXPR` is an output path expression\n   117Ôćĺstarting with the contextual keyword `output`:\n   118Ôćĺ\n   119Ôćĺ| Expression | Meaning |\n   120Ôćĺ|---|---|\n   121Ôćĺ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   122Ôćĺ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   123Ôćĺ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   124Ôćĺ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   125Ôćĺ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   126Ôćĺ\n   127ÔćĺIf the source step's output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the parsed\n   128Ôćĺstructure. If the output is plain text, only bare `output` is valid. The resolved\n   129Ôćĺvalue is converted to a string for env var injection.\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131ÔćĺIf two wires targeting the same step both map the same env var key, validation\n   132Ôćĺreturns an error (the mapping would be ambiguous). The same key may be used on\n   133Ôćĺwires to different steps without conflict.\n   134Ôćĺ\n   135Ôćĺ## The `host {}` Block\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137ÔćĺHost workflows support a `host {}` block at the workflow level to configure agent\n   138Ôćĺdefaults for agent steps running on the host machine. Keys are stored with a `host.`\n   139Ôćĺprefix, analogous to the `container {}` block for container workflows.\n   140Ôćĺ\n   141Ôćĺ```\n   142Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   143Ôćĺ  host {\n   144Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   145Ôćĺ  }\n   146Ôćĺ  ...\n   147Ôćĺ}\n   148Ôćĺ```\n   149Ôćĺ\n   150ÔćĺSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   151Ôćĺ`agent_args` override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults. The agent command\n   152Ôćĺresolution order for host agent steps is the same as for container agent steps:\n   153Ôćĺstep-level > workflow-level `host {}` > `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var > default\n   154Ôćĺ`claude`.\n   155Ôćĺ\n   156Ôćĺ## Host Workflow Example\n   157Ôćĺ\n   158Ôćĺ```\n   159Ôćĺ# .cloche/host.cloche ÔÇö runs on the host machine\n   160Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   161Ôćĺ  host {\n   162Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   163Ôćĺ  }\n   164Ôćĺ\n   165Ôćĺ  step ready-tasks {\n   166Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n   167Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   168Ôćĺ  }\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ  step prepare-prompt {\n   171Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   172Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   173Ôćĺ  }\n   174Ôćĺ\n   175Ôćĺ  step develop {\n   176Ôćĺ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   177Ôćĺ    results       = [success, fail]\n   178Ôćĺ  }\n   179Ôćĺ\n   180Ôćĺ  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n   181Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n   182Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n   183Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n   184Ôćĺ  ]\n   185Ôćĺ  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n   186Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [\n   187Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id\n   188Ôćĺ  ]\n   189Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   190Ôćĺ  develop:success        -> done\n   191Ôćĺ  develop:fail           -> done\n   192Ôćĺ}\n   193Ôćĺ```\n   194Ôćĺ\n   195ÔćĺThe `ready-tasks` step outputs JSON; wire output mappings extract fields and inject\n   196Ôćĺthem as environment variables into `prepare-prompt`. The `workflow_name` step\n   197Ôćĺdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes.\n   198Ôćĺ\n   199Ôćĺ## Execution Model"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PBzqGrRSxSxC8pWZNjvguQ","session_id":"2f8bcbbf-b8aa-4f20-9779-dee3a5fa668b","uuid":"85a9c67b-e880-4af5-9ecb-e48eee16f371"}
