[2026-03-11T00:27:32Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PBzqGrRSxSxC8pWZNjvguQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary of Cloche Project File Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly examined the Cloche project and compiled comprehensive findings from the requested files. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **FakeStore Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go`)\n\nLocated at lines 34-73, the `fakeStore` is a test double implementing the `ports.RunStore` interface with:\n- **Fields**: `runs map[string]*domain.Run`\n- **Methods**:\n  - `CreateRun()` - stores run by ID\n  - `GetRun()` - retrieves run or returns `os.ErrNotExist`\n  - `UpdateRun()` - updates existing run\n  - `DeleteRun()` - removes run from map\n  - `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListProjects()` - all return nil (stub implementations)\n  - `ListChildRuns()` - filters runs by `ParentRunID` and returns matching children\n\nThis is used in 60+ test cases throughout the executor_test.go file to mock run storage.\n\n### 2. **Config Package** (`/workspace/internal/config/`)\n\nThe config system (config.go, lines 1-116) loads project configuration from `.cloche/config.toml` with these structures:\n\n**Config Types**:\n- `DaemonConfig` - daemon settings (listen, http, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command)\n- `EvolutionConfig` - self-evolution (enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets)\n- `OrchestrationConfig` - **[CRITICAL FOR YOUR TASK]**:\n  - `Concurrency: int` - parallel workflow runs (default: 1)\n  - `StaggerSeconds: float64` - delay between runs (default: 1.0)\n\n**Loading Functions**:\n- `Load(projectDir)` - loads from `.cloche/config.toml`, returns defaults if missing\n- `LoadGlobal()` / `LoadGlobalFrom(path)` - loads from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n\nDefault config (lines 39-52):\n```\nOrchestration: {\n  Concurrency: 1,\n  StaggerSeconds: 1.0,\n}\n```\n\nThe config tests (config_test.go) show orchestration config can be customized in TOML:\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 2\nstagger_seconds = 3.5\n```\n\n### 3. **Run Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, lines 1-112)\n\nThe `Run` struct represents a workflow execution:\n\n**Key Fields**:\n- `ID string` - unique run identifier\n- `WorkflowName string` - which workflow ran\n- `State RunState` - pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled\n- `ActiveSteps []string` - currently executing steps\n- `StepExecutions []*StepExecution` - detailed per-step execution records\n- `StartedAt, CompletedAt time.Time` - timing\n- `ProjectDir string` - project location\n- `ErrorMessage string` - failure reason\n- `ContainerID string` - docker container ID\n- `BaseSHA string` - git HEAD at start\n- `ContainerKept bool` - whether container was retained\n- `Title string` - one-line work summary\n- `IsHost bool` - **[IMPORTANT]** true for host workflow runs\n- `ParentRunID string` - links child container runs to parent host run\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `Start()` - sets state to running, captures StartedAt\n- `RecordStepStart(name)` - adds to ActiveSteps\n- `RecordStepComplete(name, result)` - removes from ActiveSteps, records result and CompletedAt\n- `Complete(state)` - terminal: sets State and CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)` - terminal: sets Failed state with error message\n- `ActiveStepsString()/SetActiveStepsFromString()` - serialization helpers (comma-separated)\n\n### 4. **Task-Related Script Patterns** (`/workspace/.cloche/scripts/`)\n\nThe project implements a **task-driven orchestration pattern** with these scripts:\n\n#### **ready-tasks.sh** (lines 1-18)\n```bash\n# Returns ready, unclaimed tasks from 'bd' (task database) as JSON array\n# Usage: ready-tasks.sh [max]\n# Calls: bd list -s open --json [--limit max]\n# Output: JSON array of tasks with {id, title, description, ...}\n```\n\n#### **claim-task.sh** (lines 1-25)\n```bash\n# Claims a task by setting status to in_progress\n# Input: CLOCHE_TASK_ID env var (from wire output mapping)\n# Calls: bd update $CLOCHE_TASK_ID --claim\n# Output: JSON array [{id, title, description}]\n```\n\n#### **prepare-prompt.sh** (lines 1-21)\n```bash\n# Generates task prompt from env vars\n# Inputs: CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE, CLOCHE_TASK_BODY\n# Outputs: Combined prompt to stdout and $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\n```\n\n#### **merge-to-main.sh** (lines 1-62)\n```bash\n# Rebases cloche/run-id branch onto main and fast-forwards\n# Uses git worktree for isolated rebase\n# On conflict: aborts, preserves branch for review\n# Deletes feature branch after successful merge\n```\n\n#### **cleanup-run.sh** (lines 1-44)\n```bash\n# Removes worktree and branch from completed run\n# Attempts to close task via: bd close $CLOCHE_TASK_ID\n# Cleans up git worktree at .gitworktrees/cloche/$RUN_ID\n```\n\n### 5. **Host Workflow Architecture** (`/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`)\n\nThe orchestration workflow (main host workflow) implements a **task-pull pattern**:\n\n```\nready-tasks Ôćĺ claim-task Ôćĺ prepare-prompt Ôćĺ develop (container) Ôćĺ merge Ôćĺ cleanup Ôćĺ done\n```\n\n**Wire Output Mappings** (lines 36-40 in host.cloche):\n```\nready-tasks:success -> claim-task [\n  CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n  CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n  CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n]\n```\n\nThis extracts array index [0] and nested fields from JSON output.\n\n### 6. **Domain Types** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`)\n\n**Step Structure** (lines 35-40):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n  Name    string\n  Type    StepType            // agent, script, workflow\n  Results []string            // declared outcome names\n  Config  map[string]string   // prompt, run, workflow_name, etc.\n}\n```\n\n**Wire Structure** (lines 42-47):\n```go\ntype Wire struct {\n  From      string\n  Result    string\n  To        string\n  OutputMap []OutputMapping    // extracts JSON from output\n}\n```\n\n**OutputMapping** (lines 66-69):\n```go\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n  EnvVar string\n  Path   OutputPath            // JSON path expression\n}\n```\n\n**OutputPath Evaluation** (lines 75-115):\n- Supports JSON field navigation: `output.field`\n- Supports array indexing: `output[0]`\n- Supports chaining: `output[0].title`, `output.items[0].name`\n- Returns strings for env var injection\n\n**Workflow Structure** (lines 135-143):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n  Name      string\n  Location  WorkflowLocation    // host or container\n  Steps     map[string]*Step\n  Wiring    []Wire\n  Collects  []Collect           // fanout collect patterns\n  EntryStep string\n  Config    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **Executor for Host Workflows** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`, partial)\n\n**Executor Fields** (lines 51-61):\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n  ProjectDir    string\n  MainDir       string\n  Dispatcher    RunDispatcher              // dispatches container workflows\n  Store         ports.RunStore             // persists runs\n  OutputDir     string\n  Wires         []domain.Wire              // for output mapping resolution\n  HostRunID     string\n  AgentCommands []string                   // workflow-level agent command\n  AgentArgs     []string\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `Execute(ctx, step)` - dispatches to executeScript, executeWorkflow, or executeAgent\n- `executeScript()` - runs shell command, captures output, extracts CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- `executeWorkflow()` - dispatches container workflow via gRPC, polls store for completion\n- `resolveOutputMappings()` - reads previous step output, evaluates JSON paths, returns env vars\n\n**Environment Variables Set** (lines 93-101):\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - always ProjectDir (not MainDir)\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - path to write step output file\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - path to previous step's output\n- Plus any wire output mappings as env vars\n\n### 8. **Configuration for Orchestration** (`/workspace/.cloche/config.toml`)\n\nCurrent project config:\n```toml\nactive = true\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = false\n```\n\nThe orchestration section can be configured (defaults shown):\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 1           # max parallel workflow runs\nstagger_seconds = 1.0     # delay between launching runs\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways for Your Implementation:\n\n1. **Task System** uses external `bd` CLI (task database) ÔÇö not implemented in Cloche itself\n2. **Output Mappings** are the mechanism for passing structured data between steps\n3. **Host Workflows** orchestrate multi-step processes on the host machine\n4. **Run Persistence** uses the RunStore interface (typically SQLite)\n5. **Orchestration Config** controls concurrency and stagger timing\n6. **The Loop Pattern** (loop.go) continuously launches runs while the system is active\n\nAll absolute file paths are provided above for reference."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7e666673c7c77c46 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68255\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 71011</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f8bcbbf-b8aa-4f20-9779-dee3a5fa668b","uuid":"80237970-89f2-4083-872b-4d6396efe500","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the following files in the Cloche project at /workspace:\n\n1. The fakeStore implementation used in host/loop_test.go - look for it in the host package test files\n2. The config package (internal/config/) - how project config is loaded, especially orchestration config\n3. The domain/run.go - the Run type and its methods\n4. Any existing \"list-tasks\" or task-related script patterns in the project or examples\n\nRead these files in full.","agentId":"a7e666673c7c77c46","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary of Cloche Project File Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly examined the Cloche project a