[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZbkfrhCRMUebRcgh37pPW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# CLAUDE.md\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4Ôćĺ\n     5Ôćĺ## Project Overview\n     6Ôćĺ\n     7ÔćĺCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8Ôćĺenvironments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9Ôćĺtasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10Ôćĺ\n    11Ôćĺ**Language:** Go\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13Ôćĺ**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ## Architecture\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17ÔćĺThree binaries from one Go module:\n    18Ôćĺ\n    19Ôćĺ- **`cloche`** (CLI) ÔÇö Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20Ôćĺ- **`cloched`** (Daemon) ÔÇö Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Executes host workflows (`host.cloche`) step by step on the host machine, dispatching container workflow runs as needed.\n    21Ôćĺ- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) ÔÇö Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22Ôćĺ\n    23ÔćĺHexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24Ôćĺinterfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25Ôćĺthem (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ```\n    28Ôćĺcmd/\n    29Ôćĺ  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30Ôćĺ  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31Ôćĺ  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32Ôćĺinternal/\n    33Ôćĺ  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34Ôćĺ  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35Ôćĺ  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36Ôćĺ  host/             # Host workflow executor (runs steps on host machine)\n    37Ôćĺ```\n    38Ôćĺ\n    39Ôćĺ## Workflow DSL\n    40Ôćĺ\n    41ÔćĺSteps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    42Ôćĺbuilt-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    43Ôćĺ\n    44Ôćĺ## Project Layout\n    45Ôćĺ\n    46ÔćĺCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48Ôćĺ```\n    49Ôćĺmy-project/\n    50ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"8734a279-8744-4e80-be9e-f4f7ea56e421"}
