[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01K6FDv1Xy4LaZbR1RYDfB5z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T1ascemVFa55Ne9oY7Z7Cy","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/PROJECT.md","limit":50},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2185,"cache_read_input_tokens":14008,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2185,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"f5ef2407-66a3-4c45-889d-780df397fa6c"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T1ascemVFa55Ne9oY7Z7Cy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Next Features\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4Ôćĺ## Orchestration\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6ÔćĺWe need an orchestrator - a program whose task it is to grab the next \"ready\" ticket (from beads currently, but we'll need to \n     7Ôćĺwrap it in a general adapter for \"task tracking\" services, so that we can add later support for Jira, Linear, github issues, \n     8Ôćĺetc) and then generate an appropriate prompt (using the host's code agent) before kicking off `cloche run`. \n     9Ôćĺ\n    10ÔćĺIf `cloched`/`cloche-agent` are the workers in a factory, the orchestrator is the energy. It ensures the system continues to\n    11Ôćĺrun, delivering work to the system so long as any is available.\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13ÔćĺWhen started, it checks for any unblocked / ready work to begin.\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ`cloched` then kicks off the orchestrator (with the appropriate project context) whenever a task completes successfully.\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺ## Indicator lights\n    18Ôćĺ\n    19ÔćĺIf cloche is a factory, we need indicator lights to show when things are running well and when they are not.\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21Ôćĺ## Web Dashboard\n    22Ôćĺ\n    23ÔćĺThe main landing page dashboard should show each known project with indicator lights for status.\n    24Ôćĺ\n    25Ôćĺ## Log contents\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27ÔćĺWe need to capture _all_ output from each prompt and script, not just status changes. This will give us a log of the LLM's thoughts\n    28Ôćĺand the scripts output to help reconstruct any issues post-facto.\n    29Ôćĺ\n    30Ôćĺ## Container deletion\n    31Ôćĺ\n    32ÔćĺDon't auto-delete the containers from failed tasks. We may need them to investigate issues.\n    33ÔćĺShow all kept containers in the web dashboard (and cli tool) with an option to delete them (cli: cloche delete <container name>)\n    34Ôćĺ\n    35Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"451f0568-c0ef-4665-ad9e-9290238bf146"}
