[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01ACRtabdWkDrPPPrST4Twg1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017LARX9L4RTJbqMW3E3DDeA","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md","limit":50},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6651,"cache_read_input_tokens":16193,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6651,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"b61dcd04-3dfc-43e1-a596-66120d950d40"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017LARX9L4RTJbqMW3E3DDeA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Step Timeout Design\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ## Problem\n     4Ôćĺ\n     5ÔćĺAgent steps can hang indefinitely (e.g. Claude Code waiting on a plugin server\n     6Ôćĺthat doesn't exist in the container). The engine has no timeout mechanism, so\n     7Ôćĺthe run stays in \"running\" state forever.\n     8Ôćĺ\n     9Ôćĺ## Design\n    10Ôćĺ\n    11Ôćĺ### DSL Syntax\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13ÔćĺPer-step `timeout` key, parsed like any other config value:\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ```hcl\n    16Ôćĺstep implement {\n    17Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    18Ôćĺ    timeout = \"45m\"\n    19Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    20Ôćĺ}\n    21Ôćĺ```\n    22Ôćĺ\n    23ÔćĺAccepts any `time.ParseDuration` value (e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"1h\"`, `\"90s\"`).\n    24Ôćĺ\n    25Ôćĺ### Engine Changes\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27ÔćĺAdd a `defaultTimeout` field to `Engine` (default 30m), settable via\n    28Ôćĺ`SetDefaultTimeout(d time.Duration)`.\n    29Ôćĺ\n    30ÔćĺIn `launchStep`, wrap `executor.Execute` with a per-step context:\n    31Ôćĺ\n    32Ôćĺ```go\n    33Ôćĺgo func(s *domain.Step) {\n    34Ôćĺ    stepCtx := ctx\n    35Ôćĺ    if d, ok := stepTimeout(s, e.defaultTimeout); ok {\n    36Ôćĺ        var cancel context.CancelFunc\n    37Ôćĺ        stepCtx, cancel = context.WithTimeout(ctx, d)\n    38Ôćĺ        defer cancel()\n    39Ôćĺ    }\n    40Ôćĺ    result, err := e.executor.Execute(stepCtx, s)\n    41Ôćĺ    results <- stepResult{stepName: s.Name, result: result, err: err}\n    42Ôćĺ}(step)\n    43Ôćĺ```\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ`stepTimeout(step, default)` returns the step's configured timeout or the\n    46Ôćĺdefault. It parses `step.Config[\"timeout\"]` via `time.ParseDuration`.\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48Ôćĺ### Timeout Behavior\n    49Ôćĺ\n    50ÔćĺWhen the deadline fires:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"0e02ba3c-40d0-4b24-b0dc-c1295b7ddef6"}
