[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01CN8iMNVmdnGDaMSJEdqVR8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015QWydTCQ7ATuXe2djZXtxM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md","limit":50},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3410,"cache_read_input_tokens":22844,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3410,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"37789a32-b628-4fe1-9f47-a6bbe29d35a6"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015QWydTCQ7ATuXe2djZXtxM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Wire Output Mapping\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ**Date:** 2026-03-09\n     4Ôćĺ**Status:** Proposed\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ## Problem\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8ÔćĺHost workflow steps produce output that downstream steps need as structured\n     9Ôćĺinput. Today the only mechanism is `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, a file path to the\n    10Ôćĺprevious step's raw output. Steps that need specific fields must parse the\n    11Ôćĺoutput themselves, and there's no way to express \"extract field X from step A's\n    12ÔćĺJSON output and inject it as env var Y into step B\" in the DSL.\n    13Ôćĺ\n    14ÔćĺThis came up immediately: `ready-tasks` outputs JSON from `bd ready --json`,\n    15Ôćĺand `prepare-prompt` needs `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE` and `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY` as env\n    16Ôćĺvars. Without DSL-level mapping, every step needs bespoke shell glue.\n    17Ôćĺ\n    18Ôćĺ## Design\n    19Ôćĺ\n    20Ôćĺ### Syntax\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22ÔćĺOutput mappings live on wires, not on step declarations. A wire describes data\n    23Ôćĺflow between two steps, so the mapping belongs there:\n    24Ôćĺ\n    25Ôćĺ```\n    26Ôćĺstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n    27Ôćĺ```\n    28Ôćĺ\n    29ÔćĺThe general form:\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ```\n    32ÔćĺFROM:RESULT -> TO [ KEY = EXPR, KEY = EXPR, ... ]\n    33Ôćĺ```\n    34Ôćĺ\n    35ÔćĺWhere:\n    36Ôćĺ- `KEY` is the environment variable name injected into the target step\n    37Ôćĺ- `EXPR` is an output path expression (see below)\n    38Ôćĺ\n    39Ôćĺ### Output Path Expressions\n    40Ôćĺ\n    41ÔćĺAll expressions start with `output`, which refers to the source step's output.\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43Ôćĺ| Expression | Meaning |\n    44Ôćĺ|---|---|\n    45Ôćĺ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n    46Ôćĺ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n    47Ôćĺ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n    48Ôćĺ| `output.key[N]` | Chained: field then index |\n    49Ôćĺ| `output[N].key` | Chained: index then field |\n    50Ôćĺ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"624be4a3-c13f-4d95-96dd-866548a02bcb"}
