[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01CN8iMNVmdnGDaMSJEdqVR8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0146hUNjMaYp1wHBJ56YK5T8","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md","limit":50},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3410,"cache_read_input_tokens":22844,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3410,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"b36bb28a-b973-4082-8b6b-a9833256f37b"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0146hUNjMaYp1wHBJ56YK5T8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Project Versioning Design\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4Ôćĺ**Status:** Design\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ## Problem\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8ÔćĺAfter a self-reflection cycle mutates a workflow or prompt file, there is no record of\n     9Ôćĺhow many times the project has been evolved. This makes it hard to correlate behavior\n    10Ôćĺchanges with specific evolution events.\n    11Ôćĺ\n    12Ôćĺ## Design\n    13Ôćĺ\n    14Ôćĺ### Version file\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16ÔćĺA plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`. The file is created with value `1` on\n    17Ôćĺ`cloche init`. The daemon increments it whenever the evolution pipeline produces at\n    18Ôćĺleast one change.\n    19Ôćĺ\n    20Ôćĺ```\n    21Ôćĺ.cloche/version\n    22Ôćĺ```\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24ÔćĺContent is a single decimal integer followed by a newline, e.g. `3\\n`.\n    25Ôćĺ\n    26Ôćĺ### Increment rule\n    27Ôćĺ\n    28ÔćĺIn `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`, after Stage 5 (Audit), check:\n    29Ôćĺ\n    30Ôćĺ```go\n    31Ôćĺif len(result.Changes) > 0 {\n    32Ôćĺ    incrementProjectVersion(o.cfg.ProjectDir)\n    33Ôćĺ}\n    34Ôćĺ```\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36Ôćĺ`incrementProjectVersion` reads `.cloche/version`, parses the integer, increments it,\n    37Ôćĺand writes it back atomically (write to a temp file, rename). If the file does not\n    38Ôćĺexist, it writes `2` (treating the missing file as implicit version 1).\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺ### Read path\n    41Ôćĺ\n    42Ôćĺ`config.Load` gains a companion function:\n    43Ôćĺ\n    44Ôćĺ```go\n    45Ôćĺfunc LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)\n    46Ôćĺ```\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48ÔćĺReturns the integer from `.cloche/version`, defaulting to `1` if the file does not\n    49Ôćĺexist.\n    50Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzU8HeMxKGnzFPbbezeUQh","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"17a958d9-2345-49aa-b098-9a2d2d83a6ad"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a9bf9ec0a48e3a18c","tool_use_id":"toolu_012epjQe4jiFDSKQ49cH1EjH","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Read all changed source files","usage":{"total_tokens":62443,"tool_uses":9,"duration_ms":26650},"uuid":"d287a312-2090-4d62-be57-b564f206fbc5","session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c"}
[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012epjQe4jiFDSKQ49cH1EjH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my comprehensive review of all the files, here's a detailed summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. **internal/host/task.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Purpose:** Implements task assignment from external task trackers.\n\n**New Types:**\n- `Task` - Represents a work item with `ID`, `Title`, and `Description` fields\n- `TaskAssigner` - Interface for listing available tasks (`ListTasks(ctx, projectDir) ([]Task, error)`)\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - Concrete implementation that executes a shell command and parses JSON output\n\n**Key Behavior:**\n- Executes a configurable shell command (e.g., `bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`)\n- Parses JSON array output to extract task objects\n- Handles empty arrays and empty output gracefully (returns nil, no error)\n- Uses `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir)` to run commands from the main git worktree\n\n---\n\n### 2. **internal/host/task_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- JSON array parsing with complete task objects\n- Empty array handling\n- Empty output handling\n- Command execution failures\n- Invalid JSON error handling\n- Partial field objects (only `id` required)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **internal/host/executor.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `Executor` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by the daemon loop\n\n**New Environment Variables Passed to Scripts:**\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - The daemon-assigned task ID (only if set)\n\n**New Function:**\n- `scriptDir()` - Returns `MainDir` if set, otherwise `ProjectDir` (scripts execute from here)\n\n**Modified Functions:**\n- `executeScript()` - Now passes `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var to shell commands\n- All step types now use `scriptDir()` instead of `ProjectDir` for execution directory\n\n**New Exported Utility Function:**\n- `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir string) string` - Returns the path of the main git worktree using `git worktree list --porcelain`\n\n---\n\n### 4. **internal/host/executor_test.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Tests:**\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_TaskIDEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var is passed when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_NoTaskID` - Verifies env var is empty when not set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_UsesMainDir` - Verifies scripts execute from `MainDir` when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_MainDirOverridesProjectDir` - MainDir takes precedence\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_FallsBackToProjectDir` - Falls back when MainDir is empty\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_ProjectDirEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` always points to ProjectDir\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_NonGitDir` - Tests fallback for non-git directories\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_WithWorktree` - Tests resolution with actual git worktrees\n- `TestExecutor_AgentStep_*` - Multiple tests for host-based agent execution\n- `TestRunner_WithTaskID` - Verifies task ID propagation through host runner\n- `TestRunner_HostWorkflow_AgentStep*` - Tests agent steps in host workflows\n\n---\n\n### 5. **internal/host/loop.go** (NEW FILE - Orchestration Loop)\n**Purpose:** Manages continuous orchestration of host workflow runs with task assignment.\n\n**New Constants:**\n- `defaultMaxConcurrent = 1`\n- `defaultDedupTimeout = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `idlePollInterval = 30 * time.Second`\n- `capacityPollInterval = 5 * time.Second`\n\n**New Types:**\n- `LoopConfig` - Configuration struct with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir string`\n  - `MaxConcurrent int` - Max concurrent runs (default: 1)\n  - `StaggerDelay time.Duration` - Delay between launching runs\n  - `DedupTimeout time.Duration` - How long to suppress reassignment of same task ID (default: 5 min)\n  \n- `RunFunc` - Signature: `func(ctx, projectDir, taskID) (*RunResult, error)`\n\n- `Loop` - Orchestration loop manager with:\n  - `config LoopConfig`\n  - `runner RunFunc`\n  - `store ports.RunStore`\n  - `assigner TaskAssigner` (optional)\n  - Dedup map to prevent task reassignment within timeout window\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `NewLoop(cfg, store, runFn) *Loop` - Creates loop with defaults\n- `SetTaskAssigner(a TaskAssigner)` - Configure task assignment\n- `Start()` / `Stop()` / `Running() bool` - Lifecycle management\n- `pickTask() (string, bool)` - Selects assignable task from list, filters dedup window, returns task ID\n- `countActiveHostRuns() int` - Counts running/pending host runs for the project\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- Maintains up to `MaxConcurrent` active runs\n- Ramps up immediately on success (no backoff)\n- Backs off with `idlePollInterval` (30s) on failure\n- Supports task deduplication with expiring time window\n- Staggered launch delays to avoid race conditions\n- Goroutine-based concurrent execution\n\n---\n\n### 6. **internal/host/loop_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Start/Stop lifecycle\n- Ramp-up on successful runs\n- Double-start idempotency\n- Task assignment and passing to runner\n- Task deduplication prevention\n- Dedup expiration\n- Backoff when no tasks available\n- Backward compatibility (no task assigner = empty taskID)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **internal/host/runner.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `Runner` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by daemon loop\n\n**New Method:**\n- `RunWithID(ctx, projectDir, orchRunID) (*RunResult, error)` - Run with specific run ID\n\n**Modified `Run()` Method:**\n- Now delegates to `RunWithID()` with generated ID\n\n**Changes:**\n- Passes `TaskID` to `Executor` during setup\n- Executor uses it to populate `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n\n**New Type:**\n- `RunResult` - Contains `RunID string` and `State domain.RunState`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **internal/config/config.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `OrchestrationConfig` struct:**\n- `Concurrency int` (renamed from implicit field) - Max concurrent runs\n- `StaggerSeconds float64` - Delay between launching runs\n- `ListTasksCommand string` - Shell command to list open tasks (JSON array output)\n- `DedupSeconds float64` - Dedup window for task assignment (default: 300s/5min)\n\n**Default Values Added:**\n- `Concurrency: 1`\n- `StaggerSeconds: 1.0`\n\n---\n\n### 9. **internal/adapters/grpc/server.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `ClocheServer` struct:**\n- `loops map[string]*host.Loop` - Maps project_dir -> orchestration loop instance\n\n**New RPC Endpoints:**\n\n1. **`EnableLoop(ctx, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Enables orchestration loop for a project\n   - Creates `Loop` with config from `config.Load(projectDir).Orchestration`\n   - Configures `ScriptTaskAssigner` if `ListTasksCommand` is set\n   - Starts the loop immediately\n   - Handles:\n     - `MaxConcurrent` override in request\n     - Stagger delay from config\n     - Dedup timeout from config\n     - Task assignment setup with logging\n\n2. **`DisableLoop(ctx, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Stops and removes orchestration loop for a project\n   - Stops the loop's background goroutine\n\n**Modified Methods:**\n\n- **`Shutdown(ctx, req)`** - Now stops all orchestration loops before shutting down\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- `EnableLoop` creates `host.Runner` instances with task assignment support\n- Runner's `TaskID` comes from loop's task selection\n- Loops are stored per project for management\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Behavioral Changes\n\n1. **Host Workflow Execution**: Host workflows can now be orchestrated continuously with the daemon picking up work from external task trackers.\n\n2. **Task Assignment**: The daemon can query a shell script to get available tasks and pass them to workflow runs via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable.\n\n3. **Deduplication**: Tasks within the dedup timeout window (default 5 minutes) won't be reassigned, preventing concurrent work on the same task.\n\n4. **Concurrency Control**: Multiple host workflow runs can execute concurrently (configurable, default 1) with staggered launches to avoid race conditions.\n\n5. **Main Worktree Support**: Scripts in host workflows can execute from the main git worktree (non-linked branch) instead of linked worktree directories.\n\n6. **Configuration**: New `orchestration` section in `config.toml` controls concurrency, stagger delay, task source, and dedup window."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9bf9ec0a48e3a18c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64721\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 26655</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"09a68282-a97e-4425-8989-09b75b241357","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files completely and summarize what each one does, focusing on new types, functions, config keys, CLI flags, and any behavioral changes:\n\n1. internal/host/task.go (new file)\n2. internal/host/task_test.go (new file)\n3. internal/host/executor.go (modified)\n4. internal/host/executor_test.go (modified)\n5. internal/host/loop.go (modified)\n6. internal/host/loop_test.go (modified)\n7. internal/host/runner.go (modified)\n8. internal/config/config.go (modified)\n9. internal/adapters/grpc/server.go (modified)\n\nFor each file, note:\n- New exported types/functions\n- New config keys or environment variables\n- New gRPC endpoints or CLI flags\n- Changed behavior in existing functions\n- Any constants or default values","agentId":"a9bf9ec0a48e3a18c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my comprehensive review of all the files, here's a detailed summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. **internal/host/task.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Purpose:** Implements task assignment from external task trackers.\n\n**New Types:**\n- `Task` - Represents a work item with `ID`, `Title`, and `Description` fields\n- `TaskAssigner` - Interface for listing available tasks (`ListTasks(ctx, projectDir) ([]Task, error)`)\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - Concrete implementation that executes a shell command and parses JSON output\n\n**Key Behavior:**\n- Executes a configurable shell command (e.g., `bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`)\n- Parses JSON array output to extract task objects\n- Handles empty arrays and empty output gracefully (returns nil, no error)\n- Uses `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir)` to run commands from the main git worktree\n\n---\n\n### 2. **internal/host/task_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- JSON array parsing with complete task objects\n- Empty array handling\n- Empty output handling\n- Command execution failures\n- Invalid JSON error handling\n- Partial field objects (only `id` required)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **internal/host/executor.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `Executor` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by the daemon loop\n\n**New Environment Variables Passed to Scripts:**\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - The daemon-assigned task ID (only if set)\n\n**New Function:**\n- `scriptDir()` - Returns `MainDir` if set, otherwise `ProjectDir` (scripts execute from here)\n\n**Modified Functions:**\n- `executeScript()` - Now passes `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var to shell commands\n- All step types now use `scriptDir()` instead of `ProjectDir` for execution directory\n\n**New Exported Utility Function:**\n- `MainWorktreeDir(projectDir string) string` - Returns the path of the main git worktree using `git worktree list --porcelain`\n\n---\n\n### 4. **internal/host/executor_test.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Tests:**\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_TaskIDEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var is passed when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_NoTaskID` - Verifies env var is empty when not set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_UsesMainDir` - Verifies scripts execute from `MainDir` when set\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_MainDirOverridesProjectDir` - MainDir takes precedence\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_FallsBackToProjectDir` - Falls back when MainDir is empty\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_ProjectDirEnvVar` - Verifies `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` always points to ProjectDir\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_NonGitDir` - Tests fallback for non-git directories\n- `TestMainWorktreeDir_WithWorktree` - Tests resolution with actual git worktrees\n- `TestExecutor_AgentStep_*` - Multiple tests for host-based agent execution\n- `TestRunner_WithTaskID` - Verifies task ID propagation through host runner\n- `TestRunner_HostWorkflow_AgentStep*` - Tests agent steps in host workflows\n\n---\n\n### 5. **internal/host/loop.go** (NEW FILE - Orchestration Loop)\n**Purpose:** Manages continuous orchestration of host workflow runs with task assignment.\n\n**New Constants:**\n- `defaultMaxConcurrent = 1`\n- `defaultDedupTimeout = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `idlePollInterval = 30 * time.Second`\n- `capacityPollInterval = 5 * time.Second`\n\n**New Types:**\n- `LoopConfig` - Configuration struct with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir string`\n  - `MaxConcurrent int` - Max concurrent runs (default: 1)\n  - `StaggerDelay time.Duration` - Delay between launching runs\n  - `DedupTimeout time.Duration` - How long to suppress reassignment of same task ID (default: 5 min)\n  \n- `RunFunc` - Signature: `func(ctx, projectDir, taskID) (*RunResult, error)`\n\n- `Loop` - Orchestration loop manager with:\n  - `config LoopConfig`\n  - `runner RunFunc`\n  - `store ports.RunStore`\n  - `assigner TaskAssigner` (optional)\n  - Dedup map to prevent task reassignment within timeout window\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `NewLoop(cfg, store, runFn) *Loop` - Creates loop with defaults\n- `SetTaskAssigner(a TaskAssigner)` - Configure task assignment\n- `Start()` / `Stop()` / `Running() bool` - Lifecycle management\n- `pickTask() (string, bool)` - Selects assignable task from list, filters dedup window, returns task ID\n- `countActiveHostRuns() int` - Counts running/pending host runs for the project\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- Maintains up to `MaxConcurrent` active runs\n- Ramps up immediately on success (no backoff)\n- Backs off with `idlePollInterval` (30s) on failure\n- Supports task deduplication with expiring time window\n- Staggered launch delays to avoid race conditions\n- Goroutine-based concurrent execution\n\n---\n\n### 6. **internal/host/loop_test.go** (NEW FILE)\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Start/Stop lifecycle\n- Ramp-up on successful runs\n- Double-start idempotency\n- Task assignment and passing to runner\n- Task deduplication prevention\n- Dedup expiration\n- Backoff when no tasks available\n- Backward compatibility (no task assigner = empty taskID)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **internal/host/runner.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `Runner` struct:**\n- `TaskID string` - Optional task ID assigned by daemon loop\n\n**New Method:**\n- `RunWithID(ctx, projectDir, orchRunID) (*RunResult, error)` - Run with specific run ID\n\n**Modified `Run()` Method:**\n- Now delegates to `RunWithID()` with generated ID\n\n**Changes:**\n- Passes `TaskID` to `Executor` during setup\n- Executor uses it to populate `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n\n**New Type:**\n- `RunResult` - Contains `RunID string` and `State domain.RunState`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **internal/config/config.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Fields in `OrchestrationConfig` struct:**\n- `Concurrency int` (renamed from implicit field) - Max concurrent runs\n- `StaggerSeconds float64` - Delay between launching runs\n- `ListTasksCommand string` - Shell command to list open tasks (JSON array output)\n- `DedupSeconds float64` - Dedup window for task assignment (default: 300s/5min)\n\n**Default Values Added:**\n- `Concurrency: 1`\n- `StaggerSeconds: 1.0`\n\n---\n\n### 9. **internal/adapters/grpc/server.go** (MODIFIED)\n**New Field in `ClocheServer` struct:**\n- `loops map[string]*host.Loop` - Maps project_dir -> orchestration loop instance\n\n**New RPC Endpoints:**\n\n1. **`EnableLoop(ctx, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Enables orchestration loop for a project\n   - Creates `Loop` with config from `config.Load(projectDir).Orchestration`\n   - Configures `ScriptTaskAssigner` if `ListTasksCommand` is set\n   - Starts the loop immediately\n   - Handles:\n     - `MaxConcurrent` override in request\n     - Stagger delay from config\n     - Dedup timeout from config\n     - Task assignment setup with logging\n\n2. **`DisableLoop(ctx, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error)`**\n   - Stops and removes orchestration loop for a project\n   - Stops the loop's background goroutine\n\n**Modified Methods:**\n\n- **`Shutdown(ctx, req)`** - Now stops all orchestration loops before shutting down\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- `EnableLoop` creates `host.Runner` instances with task assignment support\n- Runner's `TaskID` comes from loop's task selection\n- Loops are stored per project for management\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Behavioral Changes\n\n1. **Host Workflow Execution**: Host workflows can now be orchestrated continuously with the daemon picking up work from external task trackers.\n\n2. **Task Assignment**: The daemon can query a shell script to get available tasks and pass them to workflow runs via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable.\n\n3. **Deduplication**: Tasks within the dedup timeout window (default 5 minutes) won't be reassigned, preventing concurrent work on the same task.\n\n4. **Concurrency Control**: Multiple host workflow runs can execute concurrently (configurable, default 1) with staggered launches to avoid race conditions.\n\n5. **Main Worktree Support**: Scripts in host workflows can execute from the main git worktree (non-linked branch) instead of linked worktree directories.\n\n6. **Configuration**: New `orchestration` section in `config.toml` controls concurrency, stagger delay, task source, and dedup window."}],"totalDurationMs":26655,"totalTokens":64721,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":48276,"cache_read_input_tokens":14126,"output_tokens":2312,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":48276},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
