[2026-03-11T00:29:45Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01796ywm8kUGnffHC5LWaYw5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Cloche Usage\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4Ôćĺworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5Ôćĺcontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6Ôćĺresults to a git branch.\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ## Core Concepts\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11Ôćĺ- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12Ôćĺ- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13Ôćĺ- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14Ôćĺ- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ## Workflow DSL\n    17Ôćĺ\n    18ÔćĺWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19Ôćĺdeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20Ôćĺno orphans, entry point exists).\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ### Minimal Example\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24Ôćĺ```\n    25Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    26Ôćĺ  step implement {\n    27Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    29Ôćĺ  }\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ  step test {\n    32Ôćĺ    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    34Ôćĺ  }\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n    37Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n    38Ôćĺ  test:success -> done\n    39Ôćĺ  test:fail -> abort\n    40Ôćĺ}\n    41Ôćĺ```\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43Ôćĺ### Step Configuration\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ| Key | Type | Description |\n    46Ôćĺ|-----|------|-------------|\n    47Ôćĺ| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48Ôćĺ| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49Ôćĺ| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50Ôćĺ| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51Ôćĺ| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52Ôćĺ| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53Ôćĺ| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54Ôćĺ| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55Ôćĺ| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56Ôćĺ| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57Ôćĺ\n    58ÔćĺA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59Ôćĺ\n    60Ôćĺ### The `file()` Function\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63Ôćĺ(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64Ôćĺtemplates:\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺ```\n    67Ôćĺprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68Ôćĺ```\n    69Ôćĺ\n    70Ôćĺ### The `container {}` Block\n    71Ôćĺ\n    72ÔćĺCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺ**Step level** ÔÇö per-step container config:\n    75Ôćĺ```\n    76Ôćĺstep code {\n    77Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78Ôćĺ  container {\n    79Ôćĺ    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81Ôćĺ    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82Ôćĺ  }\n    83Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail]\n    84Ôćĺ}\n    85Ôćĺ```\n    86Ôćĺ\n    87Ôćĺ**Workflow level** ÔÇö defaults for all steps:\n    88Ôćĺ```\n    89Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    90Ôćĺ  container {\n    91Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92Ôćĺ    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94Ôćĺ  }\n    95Ôćĺ  ...\n    96Ôćĺ}\n    97Ôćĺ```\n    98Ôćĺ\n    99ÔćĺSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ### The `host {}` Block\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103ÔćĺCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104Ôćĺwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105Ôćĺ\n   106Ôćĺ```\n   107Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   108Ôćĺ  host {\n   109Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110Ôćĺ  }\n   111Ôćĺ  ...\n   112Ôćĺ}\n   113Ôćĺ```\n   114Ôćĺ\n   115ÔćĺSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116Ôćĺ`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117Ôćĺ\n   118Ôćĺ### Wiring Syntax\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120ÔćĺConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121Ôćĺ\n   122Ôćĺ```\n   123Ôćĺimplement:success -> test\n   124Ôćĺimplement:fail -> abort\n   125Ôćĺtest:success -> done\n   126Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   127Ôćĺ```\n   128Ôćĺ\n   129Ôćĺ### Wire Output Mappings\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131ÔćĺExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132Ôćĺ\n   133Ôćĺ```\n   134Ôćĺstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135Ôćĺ```\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137ÔćĺPath expressions:\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺ| Expression | Meaning |\n   140Ôćĺ|---|---|\n   141Ôćĺ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142Ôćĺ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143Ôćĺ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144Ôćĺ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145Ôćĺ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146Ôćĺ\n   147ÔćĺIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148Ôćĺtext, only bare `output` works.\n   149Ôćĺ\n   150Ôćĺ### Retry Loops\n   151Ôćĺ\n   152ÔćĺWire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153Ôćĺ\n   154Ôćĺ```\n   155Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   156Ôćĺfix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157Ôćĺfix:fail -> abort\n   158Ôćĺ```\n   159Ôćĺ\n   160ÔćĺUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ```\n   163Ôćĺstep fix {\n   164Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165Ôćĺ  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167Ôćĺ}\n   168Ôćĺ```\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171Ôćĺ\n   172ÔćĺWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173Ôćĺ\n   174Ôćĺ```\n   175Ôćĺtest:success -> lint\n   176Ôćĺtest:success -> quality\n   177Ôćĺ```\n   178Ôćĺ\n   179Ôćĺ### Collect (Join)\n   180Ôćĺ\n   181ÔćĺSynchronize parallel branches:\n   182Ôćĺ\n   183Ôćĺ```\n   184Ôćĺcollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185Ôćĺcollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186Ôćĺ```\n   187Ôćĺ\n   188Ôćĺ`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ### Comments\n   191Ôćĺ\n   192ÔćĺLine comments with `//`:\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺ```\n   195Ôćĺ// This is a comment\n   196Ôćĺimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197Ôćĺ```\n   198Ôćĺ\n   199Ôćĺ## Result Protocol\n   200Ôćĺ\n   201ÔćĺSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202Ôćĺ\n   203Ôćĺ```\n   204ÔćĺCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205Ôćĺ```\n   206Ôćĺ\n   207ÔćĺFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208Ôćĺ\n   209ÔćĺRules:\n   210Ôćĺ- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211Ôćĺ- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212Ôćĺ- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213Ôćĺ- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214Ôćĺ- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215Ôćĺ\n   216Ôćĺ## Prompt Assembly\n   217Ôćĺ\n   218ÔćĺWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺ1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221Ôćĺ2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222Ôćĺ3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223Ôćĺ4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224Ôćĺ\n   225ÔćĺThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226Ôćĺ\n   227Ôćĺ## Agent Command Resolution\n   228Ôćĺ\n   229ÔćĺPriority (highest to lowest):\n   230Ôćĺ1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231Ôćĺ2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n   232Ôćĺ3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233Ôćĺ4. Default: `claude`\n   234Ôćĺ\n   235Ôćĺ### Fallback Chains\n   236Ôćĺ\n   237ÔćĺComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238Ôćĺ\n   239Ôćĺ```\n   240Ôćĺagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241Ôćĺ```\n   242Ôćĺ\n   243Ôćĺ- **Command not found / failed to start** ÔÇö try next command\n   244Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö try next command\n   245Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö use that result (no fallback)\n   246Ôćĺ- **Exit 0** ÔÇö use result (no fallback)\n   247Ôćĺ- **All commands fail to start** ÔÇö step returns an error\n   248Ôćĺ- **Last command crashes without marker** ÔÇö step returns `fail`\n   249Ôćĺ\n   250ÔćĺKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251Ôćĺ\n   252Ôćĺ## Workflow Locations\n   253Ôćĺ\n   254Ôćĺ**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   255Ôćĺvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   256Ôćĺ\n   257Ôćĺ**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   258ÔćĺSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   259Ôćĺdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   260Ôćĺexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   261Ôćĺfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   262Ôćĺ\n   263Ôćĺ### Host Workflow Example\n   264Ôćĺ\n   265Ôćĺ```\n   266Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   267Ôćĺ  host {\n   268Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   269Ôćĺ  }\n   270Ôćĺ\n   271Ôćĺ  step ready-tasks {\n   272Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n   273Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   274Ôćĺ  }\n   275Ôćĺ\n   276Ôćĺ  step prepare-prompt {\n   277Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   278Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   279Ôćĺ  }\n   280Ôćĺ\n   281Ôćĺ  step develop {\n   282Ôćĺ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   283Ôćĺ    results       = [success, fail]\n   284Ôćĺ  }\n   285Ôćĺ\n   286Ôćĺ  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n   287Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n   288Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n   289Ôćĺ    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n   290Ôćĺ  ]\n   291Ôćĺ  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n   292Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n   293Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   294Ôćĺ  develop:success        -> done\n   295Ôćĺ  develop:fail           -> done\n   296Ôćĺ}\n   297Ôćĺ```\n   298Ôćĺ\n   299Ôćĺ### Host Step Environment Variables\n   300Ôćĺ\n   301Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   302Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   303Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   304Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   305Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   306Ôćĺ| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n   307Ôćĺ\n   308Ôćĺ### Container Environment Variables\n   309Ôćĺ\n   310Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   311Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   312Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   313Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   314Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   315Ôćĺ\n   316Ôćĺ## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   317Ôćĺ\n   318Ôćĺ```\n   319Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n   320Ôćĺ  step implement {\n   321Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   322Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   323Ôćĺ  }\n   324Ôćĺ\n   325Ôćĺ  step test {\n   326Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   327Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   328Ôćĺ  }\n   329Ôćĺ\n   330Ôćĺ  step lint {\n   331Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   332Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   333Ôćĺ  }\n   334Ôćĺ\n   335Ôćĺ  step quality {\n   336Ôćĺ    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   337Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   338Ôćĺ  }\n   339Ôćĺ\n   340Ôćĺ  step fix {\n   341Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   342Ôćĺ    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   343Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   344Ôćĺ  }\n   345Ôćĺ\n   346Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n   347Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n   348Ôćĺ\n   349Ôćĺ  test:success -> lint\n   350Ôćĺ  test:success -> quality\n   351Ôćĺ  test:fail -> fix\n   352Ôćĺ\n   353Ôćĺ  lint:fail -> fix\n   354Ôćĺ  quality:fail -> fix\n   355Ôćĺ  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   356Ôćĺ\n   357Ôćĺ  fix:success -> test\n   358Ôćĺ  fix:fail -> abort\n   359Ôćĺ  fix:give-up -> abort\n   360Ôćĺ}\n   361Ôćĺ```\n   362Ôćĺ\n   363Ôćĺ## Container Isolation Model\n   364Ôćĺ\n   365Ôćĺ- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   366Ôćĺ- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   367Ôćĺ- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   368Ôćĺ- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   369Ôćĺ- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   370Ôćĺ\n   371ÔćĺYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n   372Ôćĺ\n   373Ôćĺ## CLI Reference\n   374Ôćĺ\n   375Ôćĺ### `cloche init`\n   376Ôćĺ\n   377ÔćĺScaffold a new Cloche project.\n   378Ôćĺ\n   379Ôćĺ```\n   380Ôćĺcloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   381Ôćĺ```\n   382Ôćĺ\n   383Ôćĺ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   384Ôćĺ|------|---------|-------------|\n   385Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   386Ôćĺ| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   387Ôćĺ\n   388ÔćĺCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   389Ôćĺhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   390Ôćĺ\n   391Ôćĺ### `cloche run`\n   392Ôćĺ\n   393ÔćĺLaunch a workflow run.\n   394Ôćĺ\n   395Ôćĺ```\n   396Ôćĺcloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   397Ôćĺ```\n   398Ôćĺ\n   399Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   400Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   401Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   402Ôćĺ| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   403Ôćĺ| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   404Ôćĺ| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   405Ôćĺ\n   406ÔćĺMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   407Ôćĺwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   408Ôćĺ\n   409Ôćĺ### `cloche status`\n   410Ôćĺ\n   411Ôćĺ```\n   412Ôćĺcloche status <run-id>\n   413Ôćĺ```\n   414Ôćĺ\n   415ÔćĺShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   416Ôćĺ\n   417Ôćĺ### `cloche list`\n   418Ôćĺ\n   419Ôćĺ```\n   420Ôćĺcloche list [--all]\n   421Ôćĺ```\n   422Ôćĺ\n   423ÔćĺLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   424Ôćĺ\n   425Ôćĺ### `cloche logs`\n   426Ôćĺ\n   427Ôćĺ```\n   428Ôćĺcloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   429Ôćĺ```\n   430Ôćĺ\n   431Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   432Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   433Ôćĺ| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   434Ôćĺ| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   435Ôćĺ| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n   436Ôćĺ\n   437ÔćĺFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n   438Ôćĺ\n   439Ôćĺ### `cloche poll`\n   440Ôćĺ\n   441Ôćĺ```\n   442Ôćĺcloche poll <run-id>\n   443Ôćĺ```\n   444Ôćĺ\n   445ÔćĺBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   446Ôćĺ\n   447Ôćĺ### `cloche stop`\n   448Ôćĺ\n   449Ôćĺ```\n   450Ôćĺcloche stop <run-id>\n   451Ôćĺ```\n   452Ôćĺ\n   453Ôćĺ### `cloche delete`\n   454Ôćĺ\n   455Ôćĺ```\n   456Ôćĺcloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   457Ôćĺ```\n   458Ôćĺ\n   459ÔćĺDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   460Ôćĺ\n   461Ôćĺ### `cloche health`\n   462Ôćĺ\n   463Ôćĺ```\n   464Ôćĺcloche health\n   465Ôćĺ```\n   466Ôćĺ\n   467ÔćĺShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   468Ôćĺ\n   469Ôćĺ### `cloche shutdown`\n   470Ôćĺ\n   471Ôćĺ```\n   472Ôćĺcloche shutdown\n   473Ôćĺ```\n   474Ôćĺ\n   475Ôćĺ## Project Layout\n   476Ôćĺ\n   477Ôćĺ```\n   478Ôćĺmy-project/\n   479ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\n   480ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   481ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   482ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   483ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\n   484ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   485ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\n   486ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\n   487ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\n   488ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   489ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   490ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   491ÔćĺÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   492ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   493ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\n   494ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\n   495ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\n   496ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   497ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   498ÔćĺÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\n   499ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   500ÔćĺÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n   501Ôćĺ```\n   502Ôćĺ\n   503Ôćĺ## Daemon Configuration\n   504Ôćĺ\n   505Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   506Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   507Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   508Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   509Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   510Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   511Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   512Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   513Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   514Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   515Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   516Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   517Ôćĺ\n   518Ôćĺ### Client Configuration\n   519Ôćĺ\n   520Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   521Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   522Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   523Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   524Ôćĺ\n   525Ôćĺ## Dockerfile Requirements\n   526Ôćĺ\n   527ÔćĺThe container image must have:\n   528Ôćĺ- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   529Ôćĺ- `git` installed\n   530Ôćĺ- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   531Ôćĺ- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   532Ôćĺ- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   533Ôćĺ\n   534Ôćĺ## Build Commands\n   535Ôćĺ\n   536Ôćĺ```\n   537Ôćĺmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   538Ôćĺmake test           # Run all tests\n   539Ôćĺmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   540Ôćĺmake lint           # Run go vet\n   541Ôćĺmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   542Ôćĺmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   543Ôćĺmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   544Ôćĺmake clean          # Remove bin/\n   545Ôćĺ```\n   546Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b83aa53c-b539-403e-957d-d27f065bd09c","uuid":"1cb9f92d-025f-46a7-97dc-ef65971a449e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** ÔÇö per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** ÔÇö defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### The `host {}` Block\n\nCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\nwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** ÔÇö try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** ÔÇö use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** ÔÇö step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** ÔÇö step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\nÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":546,"startLine":1,"totalLines":546}}}
